==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] ''[[internecinus]]'', '''[[deadly]]'''
===Adjective===
'''internecine'''

#[[mutual]]ly [[destructive]], most often applied to [[warfare]]
#:'''''[[Internecine]]''' strife in Gaza claimed its most senior victim yesterday when militants assassinated one of the most hated security chiefs there.''
#[[struggle]] within a group, usually applied to an [[ethnic]] or [[familial]] relationship
#:''The [[en:Mongol|Mongol]] people were plagued by '''internecine''' conflict until [[en:Genghis Khan|Genghis Khan]] unified them and focused their aggression outwards on other peoples.''